  "name": "leios_votes_then_hash_mismatch",
  "description": "EB-A (slot 100, hash=aa\u00d732) is offered via LeiosNotify and immediately accumulates 100 votes from distinct voters across 10 batches of 10 \u2014 deliberately above any plausible quorum threshold. The node then fetches the body via LeiosFetch; the harness responds with an empty CBOR map (0xa0) whose blake2b-256 hash does not match the advertised aa\u00d732 identifier. A conforming node must not produce a VT bundle for an EB whose body it has verified to be corrupt. The test probes whether the node eagerly forms a bundle when quorum is reached (before fetch) or correctly withholds the bundle pending successful body verification, and then invalidates the accumulated votes on hash mismatch. The verifier should observe a hash-mismatch rejection and confirm no VTBundleGenerated event is emitted for EB-A.",
